@startuml
title Git Branching Strategy

skinparam branch {
    FontSize 12
}

' Main branches
rectangle "main" as MAIN
rectangle "dev" as DEV

' Example feature branches
rectangle "feature/xyz" as F1
rectangle "feature/abc" as F2

' Development happens on feature branches
F1 --> DEV : MR → squash + FF merge\n(after sanity checks)
F2 --> DEV : MR → squash + FF merge\n(after sanity checks)

' Flow to main
DEV --> MAIN : Manual merge\n(no auto-trigger)
DEV --> MAIN : Auto merge when commit\ncontains [r] in title

' Notes
note right of DEV
  Development branch.
  Must contain only commits that passed sanity checks.
  All merges are squash + fast-forward.
end note

note right of MAIN
  Official mainline.
  Receives releases.
  Only gets changes from dev.
end note

note left of F1
  Developers branch from dev.
  Work in multiple commits.
  Submit MR when ready.
end note

@enduml
